item.description:
		In the context of the School example, we now define a query pattern that matches connected pairs of Teachers and Schools. Inside the newly created .vql file, paste the following code:



  pattern TeachersOfSchool(T:Teacher, Sch:School) = {

    School.teachers(Sch,T);

  }



This pattern includes a simple edge constraint of type School.teachers, specifying that T-Sch pairs in the match set (the result of a query) should be Teacher-School instance pairs that are actually connected by a reference of this type.
